[Gemini]: I have completed my review of this group of findings. The core vulnerability is a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) weakness in the `lxml` HTML cleaner, caused by an incomplete `link_attrs` set that is missing the HTML5 `formaction` attribute. This allows `javascript:` URLs in `formaction` attributes to bypass sanitization.

I have submitted two true positive findings that pinpoint the root cause of this vulnerability:
1.  The definition of `link_attrs` in `src/lxml/html/defs.py`, which is the source of the incomplete attribute set.
2.  The usage of this deficient set in `src/lxml/html/__init__.py`, which exposes the vulnerability to users of the library.

I also investigated the related `safe_attrs` definitions and determined they are part of the same vulnerable code path but not the root cause. The vulnerability is exploitable when the cleaner is configured in a way that relies on `link_attrs` for URL sanitization. No other distinct vulnerabilities were found.

